industry_entity.name: Indian Ocean
industry_entity.about:
Indian Ocean, the pioneers of the fusion rock genre in India, is an Indian rock band formed in New Delhi in 1990.  Susmit Sen, Asheem Chakravarty, Rahul Ram and Amit Kilam were band members till Chakravarty's death on 25 December 2009, after which Tuheen Chakravorty and Himanshu Joshi were officially inducted into the band as replacements. After the departure of Susmit Sen in 2013, Rahul Ram is the only founding member who appeared on the band's debut album Indian Ocean.

Their unique sound of Contemporary Rock mixed with classical, jazz and fusion have earned them a cult following. Some of the themes of their songs are inspired from sufi-ism, mythology and environmental issues.

They've gone out to play a slew of stand-out concerts, enthralling audiences of all ages all over the country and have performed at prestigious festivals abroad including Glastonbury and the Edinburgh Fringe.

industry_entity.name: Dualist Inquiry
industry_entity.about:
Dualist Inquiry is the solo electronic project of Sahej Bakshi, a producer, guitarist and composer.

Bakshi, who learned to play guitar at age nine, formed a school rock band with actor-musician Imaad Shah while they were at Doon School in Dehradun. Shah was the vocalist and bassist, and Bakshi was the lead guitarist of the group, which performed covers of hits by Rage Against the Machine, Green Day and Blink 182. The band split up after they left school, with Shah coming to Mumbai to study at St. Xavierâ€™s College and Bakshi moving to Los Angeles to study at the Thornton School of Music.

Since returning to Delhi after graduation, Sahej has been touring India extensively. In addition to being selected to perform at Berlin Music Week in Sept 2010, He was also ranked #1 nationally in the Burn Sasha Tour remix competition (2010) and was the 2nd Runner Up in the MTV Submerge Ultimate Pro DJ Championship 2010, held at Blue Frog in Mumbai. 

He released his debut EP Dualism in June 2011, featuring a collaboration on â€˜Qualiaâ€™ with Monica Dogra, vocalist of electro-rock outfit, Shaaâ€™ir + Func. Bakshi released his debut LP Doppelganger in March 2013 on Dualism Records.

industry_entity.name: Hari & Sukhmani
industry_entity.about:
Two individuals, one band. The duo is on a mission to create refreshing and inspiring soulful songs which is an amalgamation of traditional Punjabi music, ambient Electronica and everything in between. From traces of rap to lyrics inspired from famous Sufi poets like Bulleh Shah, Baba Farid, Kabir and Shah Hussain, the more you'll search, the more you'll find. 

They have also appeared on various TV shows and Radio Broadcasts such as BBC Radio UK, MTV Coke Studio, Star Worldâ€™s The Dewarists, Fox Travellerâ€™s Sound Trek, Tehelka Music Project and many more.

Their collaborations with artists such as Noori (Pakistan), Arshad Khan (Israj Player), Thu Le (Vietnam, Western guitarist), Trilok Gurtu (Percussionist), Fakhruddin Ghaffari (Iran, Percussionist) and Earthstage (Indian Jazz Band) have allowed their music to cut across various platforms, genres, audiences and even borders and be heard around the world.

The bandâ€™s motto is to leave behind cultural, religious, and racial divides and to bring a transformation in the society through their music.

If you haven't heard about them, you're probably  living under a rock. Go check them out!

industry_entity.name: Blue Temptation
industry_entity.about:
Nathan and Greg formed 'Blue Temptation' on 28 Jan 2010. Well, the name speaks for itself that when the band pays any song regardless of which genre, there is always a feeling involved and the â€˜Bluesâ€™ is all that comes out. There is always like a temptation to play the blues and to dwell in its warm embrace.

As session musicians, Nathan and Greg have played some gigs around Shillong, which is their home time, with well known local artists.

As time goes by and love for music grows, these two brothers decided to take their musical abilities to the next level - influencing many with the music they produce.

Shepherd Najiar a close friend and musical companion of the brothers decided to join in their musical journey a day after it was formed.

The band started out as a three piece with Greg on drums, Nathan on bass and Shepherd on guitars. 

With many gigs and shows in their book, the band came to know many people and among them, came along a friend who instantly bonded with the band. Realizing the need for a second guitarist, Greg shifted to guitars and Daryl who is the drummer from the band Polyticks, stepped in to experience the ' Blue Temptation â€˜, which is a feeling that sometimes take the band to a place out of this world â€¦

industry_entity.name: Band Stand
industry_entity.about:
Welcome to Bandstand.
A space curated to offer traditional classic cocktails complemented by fresh and simple tapas and a range of Mediterranean and world fusion inspired dishes .
It is also essentially a live music venue in the heart of the city (Delhi) located at Aurobindo market, with the sole purpose of bringing musicians together to create an ambiance filled with reminiscence of music of the days past, and some of the best talent on show today. Both curated perfectly to make you wanting for more.
The food on offer ranges from a variety of well known tapas to salads and sandwiches and a blend of your favourite bar fare choices.
It also has a large outdoor balcony area, where one can enjoy the view of the markets passers by.
And if it's just a drink at your neighborhood bar that appeals to you then the spacious bar counter is just what you're looking for.

What Bandstand offers is a chic- chilled out space to come enjoy a few classic cocktails, with some great food and even better music.
